==English==

===Noun===
'''boilerplate'''  (''plural:'' '''[[boilerplates]]''')
# A standard [[text]] used routinely, especially text of a [[legal]] or [[official]] nature.
#:''They put that '''boilerplate''' on all the warning labels.''

===Adjective===
'''boilerplate'''
# Describing text of a standard or [[routine]] nature.
#: ''The contract contained all the usual '''boilerplate''' clauses.''
===Usage examples===
'''boilerplate sincerity'''
# Accusing the user of insincere intentions
Example: after someone signing their post with '''Sincerely XYZ''', SweetFancyMoses says: "hasn't somebody already yelled at you for signing your posts?  '''Boilerplate sincerity is anything but'''."